<div class="inner cover">

  <h1 class="cover-heading">Who Am I?</h1>

  <div class="row">

    <div class="col-md-12">

      <div class="card-contact-about">

        <div class="card">

          <div class="card-block-left">

            <div class="row">

              <div class="col-md-4 col-sm-12 col-12 heading-black">

                <%= image_tag "profile.jpg", width: '100%', alt: "Profile image", class: 'profile-image' %>

                <div class="skills py-3">

                  <h5>My skills distribution:</h5>

                    <% @skills.each do |skill| %>

                      <h6><%= skill.title %></h6>

                      <div class="skill">

                        <div class="progress">

                          <div
                            class="progress-bar  bg-warning"
                            role="progressbar"
                            aria-valuenow="<%= skill.percent_utilized %>"
                            aria-valuemax="100"
                            style="width: <%= skill.percent_utilized %>%;"
                          >
                          </div>
                        </div>
                      </div>
                    <% end %>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div class="col-md-8 col-sm-12">

                  <div class="row">
                  <div class="col-md-12">
                    <p>I am a junior rails developer with a lot of mettle to become master sooner than later. I have started my codding jurney with creating Wordpress sites. They were quite easy to set up but every modyfication of existing template was a challange. I've leared how painful CSS can be but also how helpful bit of Javascript could be. I am trying to "soak" into coding by surrounding myself with quality coding content all day long. </p>
                  </div>
                </div>

                <div class="row">

                  <div class="col-xs-12 col-lg-4 col-md-5 col-sm-6 xs-mb-4">
                    <button
                      class="btn btn-primary btn-lg mb-3 button-full-width"
                      type="button"
                      data-toggle="collapse"
                      data-target="#jobHistory"
                      aria-expanded="false"
                      aria-controls="jobHistory"
                    >

                     Job History

                    </button>
                  </div>

                  <div class="col-xs-12 col-lg-4 col-md-5 col-md-4 col-sm-6">
                    <button
                     class="btn btn-primary btn-lg button-full-width"
                     type="button"
                     data-toggle="collapse"
                     data-target="#education"
                     aria-expanded="false"
                     aria-controls="education"
                   >

                    Education

                    </button>
                  </div>
                </div>

                <div class="row">
                 <div class="collapse" id="jobHistory">
                   <div class="card card-block-left card-job">
                     <p>I am a junior rails developer with a lot of mettle to become master sooner than later. I have started my codding jurney with creating Wordpress sites. They were quite easy to set up but every modyfication of existing template was a challange. I've leared how painful CSS can be but also how helpful bit of Javascript could be. I am trying to "soak" into coding by surrounding myself with quality coding content all day long. </p>
                   </div>

                   <div class="card card-block-left card-job">
                     <p>I am a junior rails developer with a lot of mettle to become master sooner than later. I have started my codding jurney with creating Wordpress sites. They were quite easy to set up but every modyfication of existing template was a challange. I've leared how painful CSS can be but also how helpful bit of Javascript could be. I am trying to "soak" into coding by surrounding myself with quality coding content all day long. </p>
                   </div>
                 </div>
                 </div>

                 <div class="row">
                 <div class="collapse" id="education">

                   <div class="card card-block-left card-job">
                     School 1
                   </div>

                   <div class="card card-block-left card-job">
                     School 2
                   </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
                </div>
                </div>

            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
